# Zotero

## Zotero Demo

## Getting Started

Visit [Zotero.org](https://www.zotero.org/)
[Downloads](https://www.zotero.org/download/)
* Desktop application
* Zotero Connector
* Optional [additional plugins](https://www.zotero.org/support/plugins)

## Desktop Application

Store metadata on books, articles, book chapters, magazines, newspapers,
podcasts, videos, reports, lectures, etc.
● Create notes nested within certain entries (great for reading notes)
● Tags
● Sync your library and notes across multiple machines (you need an account)
● Access your account through the Zotero website
● Settings for metadata and syncing 

## Zotero Connector

Once, the plugin is installed, you can easily add items to Zotero.
● JStor
● Google Scholar
● Journal websites
● Publisher websites
● Amazon.com
● ISBN numbers
● (sometimes) Directly from a PDF
● News articles 

Adds a Zotero menu to Google Docs!

## Style Repository

[Zotero Style Repository](https://www.zotero.org/styles)
All the hits — Chicago, MLA, APA, etc. — and much, much more
● Discipline styles
● Journal-specific styles
You can switch a style in “document preferences” (in the word processor)
● Updates all in-text citations
● And the bibliography!

## Word Plugin

https://www.zotero.org/support/word_processor_plugin_usage

## In-text modifications

You can make a lot of modifications within the word processor
● Multiple items in single citation
● Editing existing citations
● Hiding authors
● Adding page numbers, chapters, tables, figures
● Adding text within the parentheses (e.g. “see also”)
● “Refresh” to update modifications you make in the desktop app

## Zotero versus alternatives

Comparison chart from UChicago library
● Zotero is free
● Allows you to easily pull data on items from your browser
● Gives you access to thousand of styles
● It works without an internet connection 

## Conclusion

These are basics, but there’s more!
● [Groups](https://www.zotero.org/groups/)
● Exporting your library
● Integration with Quarto
   * Need to be in Visual mode!
● [“Locate”](https://www.zotero.org/support/locate)
● [More resources](https://www.zotero.org/support/)
● “Upgrade” your storage to support Zotero
